ğŸ”¹ What is HashSet?

HashSet stores ONLY values (no key)
And it never allows duplicates.

Real-life example ğŸŸï¸

Movie tickets:

Seat A1

Seat A2

Seat A1 âŒ (duplicate, not allowed)

Simple Java Example (HashSet)
HashSet<String> set = new HashSet<>();

set.add("Apple");
set.add("Banana");
set.add("Apple"); // ignored

System.out.println(set);


Output:

[Apple, Banana]


ğŸ“Œ Why Apple not added twice?
Because HashSet uses hashing to check duplicates.

ğŸ”¹ How HashSet Works (Simple logic)

